                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.116/95: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-09-27T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 27, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>330. Your 772, September 27, 3 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>What action has Legation taken or does it propose?</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Department does not believe that it would be advisable at this stage to
                        act on Canton’s second suggestion, namely, that an effort be made to
                        persuade the Central Government to reduce temporarily the duty on kerosene
                        to a figure which would enable imported kerosene to compete with the locally
                        distilled product. If the Central Government took such action, the Canton
                        authorities might raise other difficulties which would prejudice the present
                        negotiations of the American and British Consuls General at Canton. It is
                        suggested therefore that any action toward carrying out that suggestion
                        should be postponed pending outcome of present negotiations.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
